1) Write a short paragraph in your own words defining what a 'program' is and give one real-life example from any app you use daily (like Instagram, Zomato, or Paytm).

   A program is a set of instructions written in a programming language that tells a computer or mobile app what tasks to perform. Programs help devices solve problems and perform actions automatically.

   Real-life example: When I use Instagram, the app's program allows me to log in, view posts and reels, like photos, and send messages to friends.


